  "lines": [
    {
      "line_1based": 1,
      "serial_label": "L1",
      "text": "Tunisians Concerned Over Incidents on Algerian Border",
      "char_len": 53,
      "line_kind": "text_line",
      "line_box_xyxy": [
        18,
        10,
        566,
        24
      ]
    },
    {
      "line_1based": 2,
      "serial_label": "PB2",
      "text": "",
      "char_len": 0,
      "line_kind": "paragraphblank",
      "line_box_xyxy": [
        18,
        27,
        566,
        46
      ]
    },
    {
      "line_1based": 3,
      "serial_label": "L3",
      "text": "",
      "char_len": 0,
      "line_kind": "text_line",
      "line_box_xyxy": [
        18,
        47,
        566,
        57
      ]
    },
    {
      "line_1based": 4,
      "serial_label": "L4",
      "text": "[ ] Tunisian officials are displaying concern over what appears to be an increase in the number and gravity of frontier incidents involving violations of Tunisian territory by French forces based in Algeria.",
      "char_len": 207,
      "line_kind": "text_line",
      "line_box_xyxy": [
        18,
        65,
        566,
        75
      ]
    },
    {
      "line_1based": 5,
      "serial_label": "L5",
      "text": "",
      "char_len": 0,
      "line_kind": "text_line",
      "line_box_xyxy": [
        18,
        83,
        566,
        93
      ]
    },
    {
      "line_1based": 6,
      "serial_label": "L6",
      "text": "While there is no indication that any French elements are prepared at this time to provoke a major incident similar to last year's attack on the Tunisian border village of Sakiet Sidi Youssef, French Army units do appear to have become more active. This has been particularly noticeable in the southern desert region, where the French Army has taken an aggressive position in defending the \"rights\" of nomadic Algerian tribes which have traditionally moved freely in the barren and largely undemarcated border area. Early this year the Tunisians began cracking down on these tribesmen, whose incursions they believe are encouraged by French authorities in Algeria as part of France's effort to uphold its territorial claims in the area. These conflicting policies have already caused at least one dangerous confrontation of French and Tunisian military units and could easily lead to more serious trouble.",
      "char_len": 905,
      "line_kind": "text_line",
      "line_box_xyxy": [
        18,
        101,
        566,
        111
      ]
    },
    {
      "line_1based": 7,
      "serial_label": "BL7",
      "text": "",
      "char_len": 0,
      "line_kind": "blankline",
      "line_box_xyxy": [
        18,
        112,
        566,
        130
      ]
    },
    {
      "line_1based": 8,
      "serial_label": "BL8",
      "text": "",
      "char_len": 0,
      "line_kind": "blankline",
      "line_box_xyxy": [
        18,
        131,
        566,
        150
      ]
    },
    {
